message.content:
A jackfruit is a large, tropical fruit that can weigh up to 80 pounds.
It has a spiky, green exterior with a bumpy texture.
Once opened, the interior reveals multiple triangular-shaped sections that hold fleshy, yellow fruit pods.
The pods are surrounded by a fibrous, stringy core that is not edible.
The taste of the fruit is sweet and has been described as a mix between pineapple and banana.
Jackfruit is commonly used in vegan or vegetarian dishes as a meat substitute due to its texture.
It can be found in Asia, Africa, and parts of South America.
